article.headline: Oral Roberts 68, Lamar 50
article.story: BEAUMONT, Texas -- Shawn Glover scored 19 points and Korey Billbury and Warren Niles 17 each as Oral Roberts defeated Lamar 68-50 on Saturday night. Damen Bell-Holter added 10 points for the Golden Eagles (18-12, 13-4 Southland Conference), who never trailed. Bell-Holter and Billbury had 13 rebounds apiece. Donley Minor scored 15 points and Stan Brown 13 for the Cardinals (3-26, 1-15). Oral Roberts took permanent control of the game with a 14-1 run during a second-half stretch of 4:52. Glover and Niles had five points each during the surge, which culminated on Glover's jumper that made the score 58-39 with 4:33 remaining.
